        <abstract> 
<p>Discusses J. D. Dana’s <hi rend="italic">Geology</hi> [1849]. Pleased that the part on corals confirms his views [<hi rend="italic">Coral reefs</hi> (1842)]. Discusses Dana’s observation that in Sandwich Islands lava streams often join dikes at right angles with no cone. Retracts earlier denial of this possibility. Criticises Dana’s view of Australian valleys.</p> 
        </abstract>
